place_description: Cool deli for eclectic sandwiches & a market with beer, wine & readymade pastas, plus local breads.

reviews_data.review_text: The cutest bodega
Such a cool place to grab lunch during the week.  The sandwiches are the best!
Great bagel and coffee.
Just go here. You'll like it. Always fun and the kitchen and bar are consistently good. La Monde breakfast sandwich is incredible fwiw.
Very chill place. We arrived to live music. Our barista Karen was very helpful.  Good selection of German beers. Food never disappoints.  Parking is a challenge.
This place is expensive. I know it's in an airport and they have to give the "convenient" prices, but $17 for a sandwich that I could've ordered from a grocery store deli is just sad.
Always a good sandwich at Rhino's

Great selection of wine and beer. The coolers are also labeled with staff recommendations and beers by region. They have a good selection of NA beers and sell single NA beers, alternative beverages, and craft sodas. Reasonably priced. The live music when I went was lovely! I'll be back to eat and hang out as I just stopped by on my way to another event.

Was a stop on the party bus route. Guy told me they hated the party bus concept, I thought cool, not for everyone I suppose. Bought a 17 bottle of wine and got back on the bus. Looked at my account this morning and he had taken 37 out of my account. I realize that's not a huge amount but sketchy as hell! Check your receipt adore you leave!!!
My wife and my son and I had the breakfast burrito. Nice!  Nice people too, thank you.
Best place ever!
The food is incredible at Rhino Market & Deli. The staff is excellent and extremely helpful.
Best Rhino Market in the area by far.
Always has great food and great beer selection. Will helped me and was super nice.
What a great place to sit outside and enjoy the weather and a BANGING sandwich!! Guy named Will was very engaging and my sandwich was great!! Thanks guys!! Will be back.

This place is perfect for a quick, yet delicious, bite to eat!  The daily selections are plenty to choose from and the specials are always a treat.  As you walk to the back to place your order, you pass by a plethora of market items to peruse.  While your food is being prepared you discover a new kind of wine, your favorite healthy snack or some friends from the neighborhood.  The deli has fresh made take out as well.  From pasta salads to decadent desserts, be sure not to miss these at the kitchen counter.  There's plenty of parking as well as seating, both indoors and outdoors on the quaint patio.  Check it out y'all!!
Visited here with family from out of town and the food was amazing glad we stopped by definitely will be trying again before we leave !!!!
I absolutely love the coffee and the food and service were excellent!!
Awesome place to eat Friendly staff
Excellent service with the food to match; a friendly atmosphere with a great location. I will definitely recommend to family and friends.
Good food and very friendly staff.
Great place to stop and get a meal. The torta was delicious.

Stopped in by chance after dropping a bike off to get repaired across the street. Bartender/cashier was friendly and made a great suggestion on a blueberry cider which I tried, loved, and ordered. I liked it so much I asked if they sold it in a can/bottle. Bartender asked (who I'm assuming is) the owner/manager if they did, which they didn't, but the (again, I'm assuming) owner/manager let me fill out a tiny form so that he can try to get it in stock and contact me when it is. That's the kind of customer service that will make me remember a place and go back again. Well done Rhino!
Best customer service ! This place is awesome.
Wow! Just WowThank you for making my morning! It's been a while I don't eat a good ABLT! Excellent service! Breakfast burrito as well so good but the ABLT is so so good.
Casual location with interesting beer selection, great sandwiches, and a nice outdoor seating area.
One of my favorite places to chill on the patio. Great place to relax with a good beer and snacks.
Psychos put mustard on their Ruben and I figured I'd just order a Reuben without reading

Rhino Market is our go to pre game spot for Charlotte FC games. You can grab a 4 pack of beer and get a delicious sandwich before making your way to the stadium.

Also that new guy Cavins pretty cute
I had the stacked high on ciabatta and it was delicious. Thank you, Rhino!

First time in Charlotte and happened to stop in here to grab a late breakfast. Was pleasantly surprised by the atmosphere and friendly demeanor of the staff. (Visiting from Orlando and there is nothing like this back home) Sat at the bar area and was pleasantly surprised by the selection of beer/wine/mimosas. Alexis was super outgoing and really welcoming! Both her and Brandon had some great recommendations for how to spend my time in the QC! I could really tell that the locals enjoyed coming in and seemed like everyone was treated as family. 100% recommend stopping in!

Had a great time hanging out here on a Friday night. The sandwich on special, Mangia, was phenomenal. The peach beer on tap was also very tasty, I really appreciated them bringing the next round to where we sat. Will definitely revisit.
Great place owned by a small business owner and friend. Food is awesome and the atmosphere is terrific!
I like to go here to chill and have a beer. The people are always friendly. They do serve food, mostly sandwiches.
Really good selection of food and a great place to meet for lunch.  I gave them four stars only because it is a little pricey for the amount of food that do get.  Otherwise it is great.

One of my favorite Charlotte spots.  I miss living nearby because when we did we never bored of the Rhino.  Great staff, always friendly and helpful, amazing food.  Best breakfast burrito around, and a bargain especially since I usually enjoy it for two meals since it is so large.  Their sandwiches are all so amazing it is really hard to choose a favorite.  Great beer selection. They always have at least one dark beer on tap!
Didn't know it had to be a certain day for a sandwich. But that's cool take my money somewhere else
If you're looking for good ole fashioned deli sandwiches this is the spot!

Truly the best deli in all of Charlotte!!
Best prices, diverse menu, great service and live music or DJ most nights of the week...I mean who could ask for more?? Well being plant-based, I could ask for vegan food and, bonus, they have so many vegan options for being a deli. Even have one of the best vegan breakfast burritos I've ever had and for an unbeatable price!!
Thank you Rhino for being the best neighborhood spot to hang pretty much any day or night.
The best breakfast burrito in town
So many outstanding choices we'll laid out, tucked in a convenient place.   Customer service is wonderful!
Great deli, good vibes, good beer, wish their chicken was a little less dry. Also hope they end up selling soup earlier than 11.

Neighborhood staple. Coffee, breakfast burrito, deli sandwiches, and retail snacks/drinks. The true gem of this spot is the staff. They're awesome, friendly, and stick around. Thanks Rhino for making Wesley Heights home.
Jason the kitchen manager was the best.  Food amazing
Always friendly with a great patio.
It was a simple little store. Everyone was very kind and the bathrooms were SO clean

stopped in for a breakfast sammie and we were not disappointed. their bagels are absolutely delicious and i appreciated the amount of choices i had for a bacon, egg, and cheese sandwich. it was one of the best i've had in a long time! big plus for friendly staff and their amount of beverage/ snack offerings.

really cool place with a cool location and really nice staff! my bf loved the club sandwich but i was not a fan of the chicken torta despite some of these reviews. didn't have much flavor at all but i will definitely be back to try something else

Everything you've read about the breakfast burrito is TRUE! Randomly craving one and found this spot. So glad I came here, hands down best tasting and well seasoned. Also it's pretty big, will keep you full for hours. And their hot coffee is pretty good as well.
Overall it's a vibe. Highly recommend, you will not be disappointed.
The sandwiches were terrible, would not recommend this place.
Had the vegan burrito, quite tasty

2 reubens, mustard on side and sourdough. I got mustard and sauce on side, no kraut and tough meat. Y'all need to learn to slice deli meats. Against the grain, people! Also, listen to what people order. Thank you.
Fun selection & nice spot to grab a bite too!

It was great! The atmosphere is great for a quick meal. Dine in or takeout.  They also have grocery items if you need to pickup a few things. Staff was very friendly.

I stopped in to hear my  grandson, DJ ZAY, share his musical magic  with customers while I did a little online work. It was awesome to see and hear him "do his thing."  His style is smooth and diverse. A little funk, a little old school, a little original.

I highly recommend rhino market and DJ ZAY!
Best place for snacks, salads, and sandwiches. They also have a surprisingly good wine selection which I appreciate.
Im not a huge cold sandwich person, but this tuna salad sandwich was really good. Highly recommend.
Great sandwiches and drink selection.
Couldn't find any small bottles of water.

Long time customer, first time reviewer. This place is fantastic! They have an awesome selection of goods and the service is always great. Their deli kills it, and their new bagels take their breakfast sammies over the top. What more can you ask for from a neighborhood market
One of my fav spots. Love the Chicken Torta and Spinach bacon salad. I noticed they are on GrubHub now so I can order ahead for pick up which is very convenient.
Fast service and fresh sandwiches with a upbeat Atmosphere.  Love stopping in here for lunch while in the uptown area.
My go to quick spot for lunch and a drink!

This place slippity slaps. The Chicken Torta is my favorite sandwich here.

Their sandwiches keep getting more expensive with less protein content though sadly.
Great sandwiches! Nice place to sit and enjoy.

Don't online order here, or make your own sandwitch. They don't let you know when they don't have ingredients which they charge extra to add on, and at crazy prizes for how little they do put on.Soggy sandwitch in a size that does not fit the price. I had tomato turkey  and bannana peppers with one sad thin piece of cheese. That cost 16 dollars and I waited almost 30 minutes for it. Hit up subway
Breakfast burritos cure everything
Great food and place to grab any kind of drink you would want
The food is good, as is the vibe.  My husband loves this deli and that says something because he is extremely picky.
Love this spot! Great coffee and breakfast food, really good prices and friendly staff
Rhino quality has decreased significantly
Wonderful Breakfast

Ordered over the phone  for take out. Order was incorrect, sandwich was good but not what I ordered. Paid for what I ordered not what I got. I will try them again but will check sandwich before I leave next time.

Ordered a spinach bacon salad. My salad had no cranberries, pecans, or bacon. All it had was a huge glob of goat cheese that was unspreadable, tomatoes, and cucumbers ( cucumbers weren't even in this salad, nor any other salad that was advertised ). The citrus vinaigrette was just vinegar ( I wish I was kidding). I don't know what I was given, but someone just threw in tomato's and cucumbers on some lettuce and called it a day.
Love the sandwiches...they need more animal accomadations, leash area, water bowls, but other than that its an incredible place
Great sandwich and wine shop. I come here for lunch all the time!
Nice place for an event. Great outdoor area and good beer selection.
The food, the staff, the beer, the wine and everything else here is always top quality.  Brandon, Beth and Jill are rockstars.
Quaint dinner with overpriced sub sandwiches and a ba-zillion drinks to choose.  Incredible selection of beers and more.

Incredible sandwiches and even better views. The outdoor seating area is great to people watch and enjoy your food with minimum effort. The place inside has a lot of quirky options for drinks and food. Check out their chips! There are a ton of interesting varieties

There are a lot of supercilious reviewers of this fantastic establishment.

If you don't like music with "bad words", go learn another language.

If you feel entitled to service, get outta here!

If you don't like the occasional bad taste or bad smell, go get a personality.

If a little smoke or dance bothers you, walk away....?

If you don't see drug users on a daily basis, get out more. Hashtag caffeine.

My only criticism is they seem to only hire young, 20-something broads. Seems a little ageist.
Love this place!

I love Rhino, been going for years, but today I was turned away at 6:43 pm when I tried to order a sandwich, despite supposedly being open til 7. They said they had already shut down the grill. This has actually happened to me multiple times at this location as early as 6:30. Really bad luck to turn away a customer when you're supposedly still open.
Friendly place to pop in for a fresh sandwich or hang out with friends on the patio with a beer. My favorites are the rhino club and chicken salad.
Amazing beef sandwich! Get this over Town's barfood (overpriced and not amazing). This place has a huge inventory of cool canned beer!
Came here with our 3 young children and we had to move to an outside table because they were playing expletive music.
Go on Sundays, eat, drink, be merry, listen to Dirk spin records and don't forget to tip, everyone.
My favorite place
Pricey but a neat little market! Super friendly and helpful staff!
Get the chicken torta.
Great place for a quick bite to eat. Jill, one of the managers is always smiling and very friendly, I enjoy my conversations with her. Love their ample selection of kombuchas.
ABLT!

Good place to get a sandwich. If you come around lunch time expect a decent wait. They have a grand selection of beer, wine, and grab and go snacks.

We tried the veggie sandwich and the bread was lackluster but the flavor of the vegetables inside was great! A more wholesome ciabatta with a crust would bring it next level.
Breakfast burrito is really good!

Love how funky this spot is. I had a breakfast bagel sandwich and my boyfriend had a breakfast burrito. They were both huge and delicious. Great value! The mimosas were good too, but I LOVED the Cranberry Crumble cider beer on tap.
Great selection of craft beers and the deli sandwich's are always great! I love the chicken salad, so fresh!
This place is awesome. Easily one of Charlotte's best bottle shop/deli's. They are super friendly, keep the place really clean and the food is always consistently good!

I love this rhino market, it has everything from exquisite food, excellent bottled and canned craft beer and cider selections, some of the best snacks around, epic atmosphere, live music to djs, trivia... The whole nine yards... And one can't forget the staff always friendly and awesome and that draft selection as well . If you want a great breakfast lunch or dinner, some snacks, some libations, or just to sit back on the patio and enjoy life with a nice pint then this is your place to go!
The chicken Torta is the best sandwich in Charlotte.
A bit pricey but you can't beat the food. The breakfast burrito is the best I have ever had and the French dip is solid as well.

The food was good but a dj booth at noon made it extremely difficult to hear the staff. Then after paying I sat at the bar and the bartender preferred hanging out with the dj versus asking if I would like a beer which I did. I ate my sandwich and went to a brewery.
Great food options and an impressive beer selection as well.
Love their breakfast sandwiches

2nd time I gave this place a try. Seems whoever owns this business has lame rules and policies. 1st time was at uptown location. I arrived 10 min before their breakfast ends and was told they already shut the grill down and they made no effort to assist in any solution. Probably a year later comes 2nd try, at the morehead location. I called in a couple of breakfast orders just fine. However when I arrived without warning to learn that they don't accept cash over 20.00 and the only bill I had was a 50.00 bill on me, I received no help in the matter except an excuse that the owner has this policy. To the owner if your going to be cowardly about accepting cash I suggest your more up front about this. And hopefully adjust accordingly if a circumstance like these occur. We as people are not robots and if they would have been able to accommodate me somehow I might have been a consistent, loyal customer and supporter of your business.

Nice store and the food is good, but when an employee is not only rude, but throws an insult right in your face, I can only give a 1 star. I am 6'2" and 320 lbs and not really a small guy. I picked up my order and there was another person picking up his. The lady in the kitchen said, "Ya'll have a Happy Thanksgiving." And then looked at me and said, "You look like you are ready to eat everything!" I was shocked and said nothing and just left. Then as I was driving to work, processing how this short comment played out, I wish I would have gone back in and said something, but I had to get to work.

Such a nice little deli with a variety of food, drinks, and snacks! I would recommend trying their Chicken Torta, Hot Roast Beef, or The Big Skinny. All are packed with big flavors! They have indoor and outdoor seating too. Such a vibe!

Best place to grab the best sandwiches as well as the sweet girl cookies. The staff are super friendly and the music taste is immaculate, love coming here! I always get the Hot Sicilian with bacon added and the rosemary garlic chips. Never missed

On the market side of things, things are pretty awesome! Great selection of various local coffees, snacks, and drinks and friendly cashiers. The deli on the other hand (along with the deli in Noda) has nothing but rude workers who hate their lives and want you to feel the same. Not to mention the food I tried from the deli is lacking in both flavor and value.

Staff is wonderful and more then helpful. Lost my phone like a Dumb A$$; someone turned it in and they were attentive asking if o needed anything and when I mentioned my phone; they were quick and in action. Thank you staff!

This is an outstanding cafe. The staff are upbeat & positive.  The Rhino salad was way beyond expectations!  Fresh, delicious, and LARGE!  Monica at the airport location was making everyone's day better!!!
Absolutely delicious as always and the musicians on the patio were fantastic. My 2 year old was loving every minute of it.
Good sandwich choices
Old school cooking at its best ham egg and cheese sandwich for breakfast that was excellent
Amazing food and staff
I'm telling y'all there's no better spot in the city.
Great breakfast food, highly recommend the breakfast burrito. Staff were amazing, and they had a great selection of liquor.
Amazing selection of healthy sandwiches.

Such a great location with an awesome selection of craft beers. They also have quite a few Niche brand snacks and a really delicious selection of unique sandwiches that blend tastes in a very wonderfully unique delicious way.
Great deli, lots of local snacks and drinks

Great breakfast sandwiches, great selection of beer.  I like that you can buy them by the bottle and choose whatever you'd like! Good wine selection as well. If you need a place to sit and get some work done or just to relax Rhino Market is a solid option.

I have been going and ordering from Rhino now for 2 years. When I don't want to make breakfast for my fam I pick up the phone and order and it's done in 15min. They are always polite they suggest toppings. By the time we pick up the atmosphere is so chill we sometimes even pick up and just seat outside and eat. There Lamont breakfast sandwich is my favorite hands down. I love also experimenting on there cool teas and even CBD teas amazing. Staple in our neighborhood and our home.

They don't accept to cash. The cook came out and starrd at me after a scene ensued in the dining room, all I was doing was unpacking my back to get my bank card. I saw the cook spit into my sandwich. Obviously I did not eat it. Zero stars! Disputing the charge to

Great Food & Service!! Always with a Smile
Great happy place to have a Sandwich and just chill! Huge happy beverage selection!!

Great sandwiches, but when I ordered and tried to pay they wouldn't take cash over $20 bills.  That's all I had.  Maybe the owner should train their employees instead of refusing large bills.  Annoying.
Best sandwich in Charlotte get this it's so good will not regret getting
This place is consistently good and the employees are all so nice!
love the food and hip atmosphere! this place attracts everyone in the area and it's my go to place for amazing deli sandwiches and a large variety of drinks (and local drinks too!)
Such a cool place for sandwiches, craft beer and high quality items. It's a must for lunch, just get their early because the line is out the door by noon!

My new go to on the way home for a delicious sandwich. They have nice gluten free bread the way they toasted up you can't even tell it's gluten free. And of course an unlimited supply of beverage varieties

Quaint little deli style brewery with outdoor seating.
Lots of variety in beverages and snacks friendly folk.
Jazz Thursday evening on the patio in june.
Pet freindly atmosphere, huge parking in the back.
Great place to grab some breakfast sandwiches and beer or wine for later.
There practically every Wednesday for lunch. It's just that good.
Nice place! Great selection and very friendly staff.

Been going here for over 7 years. There is another location that's a little closer to me but I just feel a sense of loyalty to the one on Morehead. I love the people here; they're very friendly and provide a great service. Great food, solid beer and wine selection, awesome random snacks, a variety of whole bean coffee. The outdoor seating area is awesome too, especially on a nice Carolina day.

Best breakfast burrito, here and anywhere. I bring all my out of town family here and they always ask to come back. There was a time when they knew me by my Saturday morning order. ha. Certified Rhino Stan.
it gud! :3

Charlotte airport!  Best coffee and service. Those ladies made my day and started off my week right with positive amazing energy .  Monica Faulk, Juanita, Keila, Erica, Ruth, and Iesha are wonderful!! THANK YOU Rhino Market.
Rhino is my go to for lunch or a random coffee to get some work done.
Great service and selection. Very convenient to 85 and the Northside.
Wonderful little store worth getting off the highway for decent prices
Hour wait time for a breakfast burrito... it's good but not that good
Had a very quick bite here today and got to see Ron the owner who made this wonderful place a reality.
Always love Rhino market deli.  Their sandwiches are great and love the ambience.  Also live Jazz every Thursday from 5-730.
Quick service.  Great food and atmosphere.  Awesome beer selection.
Great experience!  I loved the live band. The food was delicious and the drinks were cold.
Pretty sure you can't beat their $5 breakfast burrito. Love the energy and environment here. Can't go wrong by adding an iced vanilla latte.
Good food, relaxing atmosphere

Mimosa was terrible
Witnessed bartender say he can use the cheap wine for our mimosas
Great neighborhood spot. Really good sandwiches and their beer selection is one of the best I've seen in Charlotte.
Lots of food and drink selections.
Delicious!
Deli closed an hour earlier than advertised and it was the only reason foe going
Food was great! I went back the next day after trying the Rhino Club

Very unique deli/market with a good selectionof wine. You can even eat in or on the patio and play a board game with friends. I love their breakfast options. The breakfast burrito or the oatmeal is a treat for under $5.

I would like to thank Rhino Deli for this water for my spinach salad. Had to purchase some real dressing. And the amount of water I could literally cry more tears than this. I could have spent my money somewhere else and, definitely after this I will. I understand cut backs but, cut off

Great place to grab lunch. They have a nice selection of sandwiches and salads. Can get really busy during weekly lunch rush.

You order your food at the food window, pay at the cashier after picking out some chips and drinks, and pickup at the window again once they call your order#.

Good selection of wine, beer, non-alcoholic beverages and rough grocery/drinking needs. Have been able to save a trip to the store by stopping in, very convenient.
Food was EXCELLENT!!! Staff was very cordial.
Always great customer service and delicious food.

Best sandwiches are roast beef, hot civilian, chicken torta in hat order.

Update:. Quality dropped on chicken torta  .
Had the rhino club, . Will definitely be back for another one!
Awesome food and great service!
I'm a regular at the Morehead and SouthEnd locations.  Always great food and great staff!  The poppy aoli and garlic mayo go great on any sandwich.
Fast &  delicious
Delicious lunch spot
Good food options
Such a wide selection of drinks, both with and without alcohol. Food was good and prepared quickly.  Wish they had one close to my house.
This place makes a great pastrami sandwich!
Clean friendly service.  Food was delicious. Sell alot of different items all kinds of beer and wine
Very friendly staff!
Chill and relaxed atmosphere, with eclectic patrons, pleasant staff,  and a good selection of choice bevs.
Was given the wrong salad than what I ordered. Call back the said the didnt have that salad. I pointed it on the menu. Any other time a 5 star experience.
I enjoy breakfast at this restaurant it's real laid back customer service is great
Excellent service delicious food
Good and vegan  friendly.
Awesome store, that has a little bit of everything, and supports so many local goods as well! Sandwiches are great. Good vibe, location, and people.
A breakfast sandwich with coffee for less then $10? Sign me up!

It's ok. A decent, but overpriced sandwich and grocery store. I come here largely due to convenience a few times a month since it's conveniently located and pretty quick service. Nothing to write home about, but a decent spot nonetheless.
Great service for lunch despite being very busy.
Best sandwiches in town!
Nasty and unclean. I saw one of the kitchen staff rub his nose and then make food. When I told the lady at the bar register she said that didn't happen. This place is disgusting.
Great food great atmosphere

I ordered sandwiches for 10 people ahead of time and was able to quickly pick it up. Thre sandwiches were really good. The only negative is that they gave us 4 peanut butter cookies and no chocolate chip cookies. That is a foolish choice to make without asking me. First because they did not ask if anyone had peanut allergies. Two, only one person in our group liked peanut butter cookies. A wiser choice would have been to ask me beforehand if I wanted a peanut butter cookie or if anyone had food allergies.
Great sandwich spot! Great outdoor seating! Great selections of adult drinks and craft drinks. Hopefully we can get out cannabis wine in their stores! Stay blessed!

I have a medical condition with my lungs I was asked to put a mask on so I very politely said no thank you I can go somewhere else if you want but I don't wear those. The girl took it personally like I was trying to argue and was frustrated that the threat of not serving me can't work since I had already decided I wouldn't spend money here. She then childishly demanded I give the mask back bc "they're not free" (ironically she had just handed it to me for free) No one has ever been rude to me here until today and personally it's not anyone's business what medical issues I face. If you want to wear a mask and think it helps thats great. Good for you. But for the rest of us that need an inhaler to walk up on flight of steps (plus my claustrophia) it's really ridiculous. You aren't saving the world your just over stepping your boundaries with peoples personal health decisions and Its not right. The stupid have taken over the planet.
Awesome sandwich! Will definitely go again!
Cool little place. Good food. I asked the woman taking my order what her preference is between two options, she jumped in and gave me her honest opinion and it didn't disappoint. I love that.
Delicious food!  Friendly staff!  Great drink selection - alcoholic and non-alcoholic!  Love the feel of this place!  Will definitely be back!
Love it. Went almost every day when we lived closer. The worst part of moving to Cotswold is being further away from Rhino.
Horrible sandwich !!!
Wow, what cool place. people there were really nice, and the food was extremely tasty!!!
Our favorite lunch spot and for afternoon beers
Excellent service and sandwiches. Obviously very well managed.
Slow. Sandwich was fair and no more.
Always love this place times of food are getting a bit confusing.
Wow, stopped here on our last day in Charlotte. Great breakfast, super nice outdoor seating to enjoy it.
Reuben was very good. People were friendly.
Rhino Market offered a wide variety of merchandise and also a great menu of food to take out or dine in as well. Suggest any one in Charlotte to visit Rhino Market for a great experience.

Rhino Rocks!
Keeping it cool
*for serious coffee connoisseurs* Good cup of coffee with chill soulful ambiance. Staff is super friendly and welcoming. I'll definitely double back on my next trip to Charlotte!
English muffin breakfast sandwich tasted great!  Like homemade.
Great sandwiches, fast service, neat, niche drinks. Give it a whirl!
Loved my lunch!
Yummy deli
Great selection of products and the staff was friendly
Mushroom omelette with cheese  and Oats today.. Very good!

Best Rueben in North Carolina. Very friendly and helpful staff. Great menu. Large portions so you really get your money's worth. Wonderful seating indoors and outdoors. Wide drink selection and very good prices. Loved my very fist visit. I told them they did an excellent job with that Rueben.
Delicious deli food and a ton of beverage options. The tomato rice soup was fantastic.
Nice chill spot for food and drinks. Good music playing,chicken torta is a must have
Always good beer and sandwiches are great.    They also have alot of different snacks that you can't find at grocery stores.
The Reuben is excellent.
I absolutely love Rhino Market. Great snacks, sundries and wonderful food! The staff is also kind and friendly
Good variety of snacks and wine.
Super fast . Great food. Great staff!
Little pricey on the IPA , but deli sandwich was good , playing good music , Nice Vibe
I don't know why this place forgets to put salad dressing in my salad... Everytime!!
My local fav for a beer and a sammi. The breakfast is really good too
Great little place, grab coffee or beer or a snack etc. Sit inside or outside.

Very impressed with the wine selection and prices are decent
9/10
I will return.
Friendly staff and clean store
Best sandwiches and very chill atmosphere

A really great deli. With a bit more for adults. This Reuben was great. I suggest the beef. Pastrami is ,also, a good choice. Rhino deli is a must and my go to lunch spot for a work week in Charlotte.
Good sandwiches and salads. They have a pretty large selection of beer and wine as well.
Great sandwiches
Great food. Interesting place. We will return.
Love the items!
Fun store great food.
Good lunch spot and beer selection. Staff was very nice.
Hot roast beef. Enough said. One of the best sandwiches in Charlotte.
Great pastrami sandwich
Go to place while in Charlotte.
Looking to grab a yummy salad or sandwich and a local brew -- This is your spot!
Fantastic beer selection.  Very friendly too!
Good food great beer selection and friendly staff.
Fast friendly service
My favorite location. Clean, casual, friendly, and reliable, with plenty of parking.
Place was awesome got a torta and soup, it was quick and hot. Will be going back for more
Very tasty sandwiches and really good alcohol selection too. Highly recommend to get the Rhino Club sandwich.
Not only does this place have the best food, but the environment and staff is awesome too. On lunch from the office or construction,  they always hook me up and are open.
I had a great Italian sandwich!
This place is great for a wrap and a drink! A friend took me here while I was visiting from out of state and it was a great lunch.
Good hot roast beef sandwich
Best staff ever! Y'all are killing it
Great sandwiches and beer. Thursday lunch special is awesome.
Staff is very friendly and food was great!
Great local shop with excellent sandwiches and beer selection!
Lady Juanita was so courteous and kind she even helped me find something i would like considering the fact that im a vegan , good prices + good customer = returning customer
Love their breakfast burritos!!
Love this place until I recently went and saw all the employees in the kitchen not wearing face coverings. Please fix! Tried to reach out but no contact form on site.
The aioli is on point. Plus the thinly sliced cucumbers are something God himself orchestrated.
Love this place every thing is fabulous. I have not gotten anything i have not like. Its so fresh tasting and the people are so nice
Sandwiches are great
